      },
      "date": "2022-08-05 19:31:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nThe patch seems reasonable, but I was curious about your use of conns_per_peer with IB. Is that for OPA or Mellanox?  It is pretty normal for OPA to need this, but I've never heard of it being used for Mellanox, and wonder if I'm missing something.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d1f850aefec1d22f2fc7816d9c7377f849743f69",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2022-08-05 20:06:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> The patch seems reasonable, but I was curious about your use of\n > conns_per_peer with IB. Is that for OPA or Mellanox?  It is pretty\n > normal for OPA to need this, but I've never heard of it being used\n > for Mellanox, and wonder if I'm missing something.\n\nYeah, we don't see any benefit with hardware RoCE either, but with this patch we see some performance gain with Soft-RoCE.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
